              "Description": "The Prevention Program 3 applies to all manufacturing operations at the facility.  Since Westlake considers these operations to be a single covered process, implementation of the prevention program does not distinguish between process units at the facility.  Some Process Safety Management (PSM) and prevention program elements are applied separately to individual process areas at the facility, such as unit-specific process safety information, process hazard analyses, and operating procedures.  Other elements are applied on a facility-wide basis,with no distinctions between process areas, such as hot work permit requirements, the management of change program, and mechanical integrity.\n\n\n\nWestlake maintains compliance with all elements of OSHA 1910.120, PSM, and other programs: Vehicle Entry SA, Critical Spares, Equipment Painting, Internal Safety Audits, Scheduled Maintenance Turnarounds, Emergency Shutdown Drills, Environmental Area Monitoring.  \n\n\n\nAlso a part of the Westlake Monomers/CA&O Prevention Program is a series of fire hydrants and water cannons throughout the facility.  Heat activation devices (HAD's) in conjunction with sprinkler systems are present in areas of the facility with potential flammable hazards.  Process areas are equipped with curbed concrete pads and dikes.  The facility program includes an extensive employee training program and 24-hour surveillance in all process areas.  \n\n\n\nThis facility is ISO 9002 certified.",
